# Project Context
QR/NFC Table Ordering SaaS Platform
- Next.js 14+ App Router
- Tailwind CSS v3+
- Supabase (PostgreSQL, Auth, Storage)

# Database Schema & Structure
1. `restaurants`: Master record for venues (`id`, `slug`, `plan`, `is_active`, `currency`, `languages`).
2. `staff`: Restaurant employees (`id` matches `auth.users.id`, `restaurant_id`, `role`, `display_name`).
3. `tables`: Physical tables with NFC/QR URLs (`id`, `restaurant_id`, `table_number`, `status`).
4. `menu_items`: Products (`id`, `restaurant_id`, `category`, `type` -> 'food' | 'drink', `price`).
5. `orders`: Customer tabs (`id`, `restaurant_id`, `table_id`, `order_number`, `status`, `session_id`).
6. `order_items`: Order line items (`id`, `order_id`, `menu_item_id`, `type`, `quantity`, `unit_price`).

# Roles & Routing
Users are routed based on their `role` in the `staff` table. Ensure protective middleware guards.
- Kitchen, Bar do not have screens (thermal print only).
- `cashier` routes to `/[slug]/cashier` (iPad terminal handled)
- `owner` routes to `/[slug]/dashboard` (Admin interface)
- `admin` routes to `/admin`

# UI & Tailwind Design System
Never use hardcoded hex values. Always use our custom Tailwind color palette:
- `brand`: 50, 100, 200, 300, 400, 500, 600, 700, 800, 900
- `accent`: 400 (Gold), 500 (Gold dark), 600 (Gold deeper)
- Examples: `bg-brand-100`, `text-accent-500`

Animations:
- Utilize `framer-motion` for complex choreographed layouts.
- Utilize `@formkit/auto-animate` for zero-config list modifications.
- Custom tailwind classes available: `animate-fade-in`, `animate-fade-up`, `animate-scale-in`, `animate-slide-right`, `animate-shimmer`

Shadow Tokens:
- `shadow-premium`, `shadow-card`, `shadow-elevated`
